{{Italic title|reason=[[:Category:Japanese words and phrases]]}}
[[File:Japanese flower arrangement 50, Ikebana- いけばな.jpg|thumb|Large ''Mishō-ryū'' arrangement]]
[[File:Bezoekers van het museum kijken toe, Bestanddeelnr 925-5955.jpg|thumb|Demonstration of ''Mishō-ryū'' masters at the [[Stedelijk Museum Amsterdam]] during the [[Floriade 1972]]]]
{{nihongo|'''''Mishō-ryū'''''|未生流|}} is a school of ''[[Ikebana]]'', or [[Japan]]ese [[Floral design|floral art]].

== History ==
It was established by Ippo Mishosai in 1807 in [[Osaka]]. He established the defining [[philosophy]] and style of the school.<ref name="ikebanahq">{{cite web|url=http://www.ikebanahq.org/misho.php|publisher=ikebanahq.org|title=Ikebana International|accessdate=2016-11-24}}</ref>

The traditional style is called ''kakubana'' (格花), and the modern style is called ''shin-ka'' (新花).

